      <category domain="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#">Recover from autochk.exe error</category>
      <title>What is 'Autochk.Exe Not Found' Error and How to Recover</title>
      <description>&lt;div dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;" trbidi="on"&gt;&lt;div style="color: black; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;'Autochk.exe not found' error is much frustrating and may throws heavy damage to your system. Most PC users influenced with similar types of errors and ends with huge data loss. So if you are the one facing errors related to 'Autochk.exe error' and don't compromise to &lt;a href="http://datarecoverymethods.blogspot.in/2011/10/lost-valuable-data-here-is-solution.html" target="_blank"&gt;loose your valuable data&lt;/a&gt;, you should continue reading this article.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="color: black; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;What is 'Autochk.exe' &amp;amp; how it affects your system&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="color: black; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is an inbuilt part of Microsoft operating systems which gives functionality to revert core system settings back to their original state and to backup where necessary. Autochk.exe is a non essential system process but shouldn't be terminated unless suspected to be causing problem. Since most software programs uses 'Autochk.exe' to write data on system's registry, it's possible that registry can accumulate invalid entries which may leads to system failure issues.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="color: black; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;b&gt;Is autochk.exe can be Threat?&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="color: black; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you find autochk.exe somewhere else rather than its originating place (C:\Windows\system32\autochk.exe), most likely that it could be Trojan, spyware, malware or any other types of virus and your system may become inaccessible or shows black screen anytime.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="color: black; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;To Fix Corrupted registry now, &lt;a href="http://www.stellarinfo.com/data-safety-eraser/registry-manager/registry-cleaner.php" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"&gt;Download Registry Cleaner Software&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="color: black; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;How Can I Fix 'Autochk.exe' Error?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="color: black; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;b&gt;Method 1: &lt;/b&gt;Possible reasons behind 'Autochk.exe not found' error could be misplaced or deleted autochk.exe files. To replace the file again, follow steps mentioned below:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="color: black; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul style="color: black; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;Insert Windows installation CD in combo drive and explore folder 'i386'.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;You will find there a file named 'autochk.exe', you have to copy and past it on Windows system 32 folder. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;Restart the System&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div style="color: black; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Method 2: &lt;/b&gt;Besides registry entries or deleted autochk.exe files, bad hard drive or corrupt partition file system may also leads to this error. To fix hard drive related errors, you have to: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul style="color: black; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;Open CMD prompt &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;Write chkdsk /f and hit enter&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;This will scan hard drive and fix errors or critical &lt;a href="http://datarecoverymethods.blogspot.in/2011/07/advanced-data-recovery-service-to-get.html" target="_blank"&gt;hard drive issues&lt;/a&gt; if any.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div style="color: black; font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;If the problem still persists or error messages continue to appear, most likely that corrupted system's registry causing the problem. To fix this, you can download registry Manager and starts a quick scan. Doing this will fix invalid registry entries and system will start to work perfectly as before. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/4453101382727517102-2823830408640672905?l=datarecoverymethods.blogspot.com' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/data-recovery/Data_Recovery-What_is_AutochkExe_Not_Found_Error_and_How_to_Recover.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <link>http://datarecoverymethods.blogspot.com/2012/05/what-is-autochkexe-not-found-error-and.html</link>
      <author>noreply@blogger.com (Oliver Powell)</author>
