      <category domain="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#">Fix rundll32.exe error</category>
      <title>How to Fix “rundll32.exe” Error in Easy Steps</title>
      <description>&lt;div dir="ltr" style="text-align: justify; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial;" trbidi="on"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:100%;"&gt;Rundll32.exe is the most frustrating and annoying error which generally occurs while playing games, accessing computer programs etc. on your PC. It results in improper system shutdown, annoying pop- up windows; “rundll32.exe is missing”, “can't able to locate rundll32.exe” etc. Most of the users also suffer from data loss situation just because of ignoring this error. It doesn’t matter whether you know about this error or not, but fixing it is really important to maintain stability and integrity of your system.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;b&gt;What is rundll32.exe?&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Rundll32.exe is a hosting process of Windows services which is highly used in calling DLL (Dynamic Link Library) files and save as much as information on computer’s memory. It mainly resides at C:\Windows\System32 folder in Windows. You can check it by opening task manager's process tab.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:100%;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class="separator"   style="clear: both;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;color:black;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:100%;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-ftylVYrg3gs/TzIyMn_C4oI/AAAAAAAAAGI/9bpNZXhJGus/s1600/rundll32.exe.png" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"&gt;&lt;img src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-ftylVYrg3gs/TzIyMn_C4oI/AAAAAAAAAGI/9bpNZXhJGus/s320/rundll32.exe.png" border="0" height="320" width="300" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:100%;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:100%;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Cause of rundll32.exe errors?&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Rundll32.exe error is associated with system32.dll file and comes when some software or hardware does not respond properly apart from this faulty system32.dll files; virus attack, registry corruption or malicious programs are also leads to this error.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Let’s have a look on some of the rundll32 error types:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;i&gt;“rundll32.exe has generated errors and will be closed by Windows.”&lt;br /&gt;“rundll32.exe failed to initialize.”&lt;br /&gt;“rundll32.exe is missing.”&lt;br /&gt;“explorer.exe class not registered.”&lt;br /&gt;“Windows host process (Rundll32) has stopped working.”&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:100%;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:100%;"&gt;And so on…&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;b&gt;Fix rundll32.exe errors in Windows&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;There are lots of reasons and solutions accordingly. Based on some well known factors, I'm suggesting you some trusted methods to fix rundll32.exe errors:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;ul   style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;color:black;"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:100%;"&gt;Uninstall any recently installed software application and in the mean time try to update your system driver as well. Sometime, due to corrupted software application, you may experience this error.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:100%;"&gt;Ensure that the file named rundll32.exe exists in the system32 folder with the same name.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:100%;"&gt;If rundll32.exe not exists, search in your system hard drive partitions. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:100%;"&gt;If you still failed to locate the missing rundll32.exe files, then copy it from any other system with same version of OS in your system.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:100%;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Note: If you are not a professional user then don’t ever try to do this; it may cause data loss in your system.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I always advice users to use any trusted third party software to fix your registry problems.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:100%;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;table class="tr-caption-container" face="Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif" color="black" style="margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; text-align: left;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;&lt;tr align="right"&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.stellarinfo.com/data-safety-eraser/registry-manager/registry-cleaner.php"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:100%;"&gt;&lt;img src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-6Gtj3yHcY7o/TzIzi3Q73vI/AAAAAAAAAGQ/chfGpHLcas0/s1600/FIX+Rundll32.exe+error.png" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" border="0" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class="tr-caption" style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:100%;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:100%;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;ul   style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;color:black;"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:100%;"&gt;Download &amp;amp; run the &lt;a href="http://download.stellarinfo.com/stellar/StellarPhoenixRegistryManager.exe"&gt;best registry cleaner software&lt;/a&gt; and fix corrupted registries with ease. Anyone can use, doesn’t require any technical knowledge to operate it.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:100%;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;b&gt;PS:&lt;/b&gt; Except all these possible solutions, it’s advisable to take a regular backup of your important data for preventing the data loss conditions. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/4453101382727517102-7108104965333923394?l=datarecoverymethods.blogspot.com' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/data-recovery/Data_Recovery-How_to_Fix_rundll32exe_Error_in_Easy_Steps.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;